Agency Report Vice President Yemi Osinbajo has said that the legacy of determined, proud and assertive black emancipation left by late Robert Mugabe of Zimbabwe will live long in the hearts of Africans. Mr Osinbajo’s spokesman, Laolu Akande, in a statement on Saturday in Abuja, said the vice president conveyed the message on the condolence register for Mr Mugabe at Harare International Airport. Mr Osinbajo was in Zimbabwe to represent President Muhammadu Buhari at the state funeral of Mr Mugabe. “Nigeria most respectfully condoles with the Republic of Zimbabwe on the passing of her President, Robert Mugabe – who led the republic and her people to freedom and majority rule – alongside so many other patriots. Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook 